Preheat oven to 425Â°F with rack in upper third. Butter a 1 1/2-quart gratin or other shallow baking dish. Whisk together eggs, butter, 7 tablespoons sugar, zest, and nutmeg in a large bowl until well combined, then stir in apples. Cook noodles in a large pot of salted boiling water until al dente, about 5 minutes. Drain noodles, then toss well with apple mixture. Spread in baking dish and sprinkle with remaining tablespoon sugar. Bake kugel until top is golden, about 30 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.